Marketing Modes explanation (full overhaul):

Add a note feature where users can leave sticky notes such as "Check competitor's LinkedIn post" anywhere on the screen and it would stay on the marketing page until deleted and also auto populate in the Tasks page in a Notes tab.

- Autopilot:
There is a three way toggle at the top of the marketing agent to turn on full autopilot mode
When on:
Agentic loop runs every 12 hours automatically
Marketing agent involves two components: insight and implementation
When agentic loop runs- marketing report is generated by the user, all social and digital content is analyzed and insights are presented
These insights take into account any missing media outlets, any media outlets with no content
Market analysis also involves field including insights from all available media outlets: if Instagram is connected market analysis report should include followers, views, recent activity, and other information available from meta. agent should judge what is important such as values that are 0 falling or rising, old posts may not be as relevant as new posts unless an old post is getting new activity. For website (if connected), market analysis report should present views, engagement, etc. For other social media, same thing as described for instagram. for email, any leads or losses generated from email blasts, newsletters, or cold emails. If a media channel is not connected, it should have no field, if a media channel is connected it should have a field.
Next in the market analysis report, should be a general market analysis: what is happening in the world, are there competitors, how are competitors doing, etc.
Next in the market analysis report, there should be suggestions for campaigns to run based on all of these stats, i.e. the stats should correspond to the suggestions. Suggestions should be small and focused on instant implementation. If it is found that posting of competitors is every day and user's business has been posting every 2 days, the suggestion should not be general like post every day, it should be post today and then the rationale can be that user should post every day.

In autopilot, suggestions should automatically move from left side with market analysis report to the right side which is the campaign manager. They should be automatically run one by one with a progress bar and active tasks being shown as they are running. No user selection or button pressing should be involved except for a pause and remove button. Campaigns should be small enough to run in 15 minutes, if campaign requires more than 15 minutes another identical campaign should be launched instead of the same campaign running for 30 minutes. Campaigns should detail what tasks they are running in a drop down of the campaign field, these running tasks should autopopulate in the Tasks page. These changes automatically populate any media channel involved automatically without user input: website changes, instagram changes, tiktok changes, email sending and responding, twitter/x posts, and in the future any others. After a campaign is run, the campaign should stay in a "Run Campaigns" field where the progress bar continues as the campaign reaches the goal that it promised to. When the goal is reached it should be moved into "Archived Campaigns"- a drop down field at the bottom of the page. 

Future campaigns are generated based on additional insights from archived campaigns such as success rates, time, growth, and goal achievement. Future campaigns are based off of successful campaigns and unsuccessful campaigns (those that were completed but did not reach the goal and were removed or skipped from "Run campaigns" early) are suggested less frequently.

Even in auto mode, there is still the ability to make a custom campaign, require the same fields as an auto generated campaign and run the same way an auto-generated campaign would- fully autonomously without any further user input.

- Guided: 
The middle section of the toggle at the top is guided mode
When on:
Agentic loop is run by user manually. User is prompted to run the loop through a notification every 12 hours.
Marketing agent involves two components: insight and implementation
When agentic loop runs- marketing report is generated by the user, all social and digital content is analyzed and insights are presented
These insights take into account any missing media outlets, any media outlets with no content
Market analysis also involves field including insights from all available media outlets: if Instagram is connected market analysis report should include followers, views, recent activity, and other information available from meta. agent should judge what is important such as values that are 0 falling or rising, old posts may not be as relevant as new posts unless an old post is getting new activity. For website (if connected), market analysis report should present views, engagement, etc. For other social media, same thing as described for instagram. for email, any leads or losses generated from email blasts, newsletters, or cold emails. If a media channel is not connected, it should have no field, if a media channel is connected it should have a field.
Next in the market analysis report, should be a general market analysis: what is happening in the world, are there competitors, how are competitors doing, etc.
Next in the market analysis report, there should be suggestions for campaigns to run based on all of these stats, i.e. the stats should correspond to the suggestions. Suggestions should be small and focused on instant implementation. If it is found that posting of competitors is every day and user's business has been posting every 2 days, the suggestion should not be general like post every day, it should be post today and then the rationale can be that user should post every day.

In guided mode, suggestions can be manually moved from left side with market analysis report to the right side which is the campaign manager. They should be manually run one by one by the user. Each campaign then generates tasks and a progress bar, each task should be manually run by the user and the user should mark them complete. Progress bar should reflect completion of tasks. Active tasks should autopopulate in the tasks page. When a task is selected to run, instructions or content should be provided for all forms of media. For example, website content changes with direct items to switch for other items, instagram caption and post idea, tiktok video idea and caption, email content and subject, twitter post, etc.. There should be a skip and remove option in guided mode for tasks and campaigns. Campaigns should be small enough to run in 15 minutes, if campaign requires more than 15 minutes another identical campaign should be suggested to run instead of the same campaign taking 30 minutes for a user to complete. Active tasks should populate in the tasks page. After tasks are completed or user skips tasks or whole campaign, the campaign should populate in the "Run campaigns" field where the progress bar continues as the campaign reaches the goal that it promised to (which is identified through future runs of the market analysis report and reflected in the progress of all campaigns), When the goal is reached it should be moved into "Archived campaigns"- a drop down field at the bottom of the page.

There is still the ability to make a custom campaign, require the same fields as an auto generated campaign and run the same way an auto-generated campaign would- presenting all necessary steps and content with the user manually implementing it.

- Manual: The left most setting of the toggle at the top is manual mode
When on:
The main features are available more as a tracking tool.
An agentic loop is not available to run to users, but their media channel insights (from the management agent where they input them or overview where they are present) are populated for them to review in a "Basic Marketing Overview" and based on these inputted stats, general suggestions are available such as any missing media outlets, any media outlets with no content.
Next in the Basic Marketing Overview, should be a general market analysis: what is happening in the world, are there competitors, how are competitors doing, etc.
Next in the Basic Marketing Overview, there should be general suggestions for campaigns to run such as creating a media channel that does not exist or creating a post/page/newsletter if it doesn't exist. It should be noted that further insights are only available in guided and autopilot mode.

In manual mode, these general suggestions can not be moved to the right side which is the campaign manager. Instead a user should be prompted to create a campaign. They should have all of the same fields available to them such as campaign name, outlet, action, tasks, goal, timeframe (which will then guide the progress bar as well as tasks completed). The user then saves this campaign. They are able to activate a task, the task has small suggestions such as general prompts or ideas. When a task is active it is automatically populated in the tasks page. A user then manually checks off a task when complete, and also has the ability to skip or remove a task and campaign. Progress bar reflects task completion and timeline. After tasks are completed or user skips tasks or whole campaign, the campaign should populate in the "Run campaigns" field where the progress bar continues as the campaign reaches the goal that it promised to (based on inputted stats in the Overview or Management page). When the goal is reached, it should be moved into "Archived campaigns"- a drop down field at the bottom of the page.




